cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CY, cs.HC. 

This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) techniques applied to electronic health record (EHR) notes to identify important medical terms for patients. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language) which deals with NLP and its applications. The paper also involves information retrieval (IR) techniques to rank the importance of terms, which makes cs.IR (Information Retrieval) another likely category. The use of ensemble ranking and biased random walk algorithm falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with healthcare applications, which makes cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) possible categories.
